<h1>JavaScript Assignment Operators Guide</h1>

<p>JavaScript assignment operators are tools for assigning values to variables. There are various types of assignment operators, such as:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Shift Assignment Operators</li>
  <li>Bitwise Assignment Operators</li>
  <li>Logical Assignment Operators (included in ES2020)</li>
</ul>

<h2>Common Assignment Operators</h2>

<h3>The = Operator</h3>
<p>This is a simple assignment operator that assigns a value to a variable. For example:</p>
<pre>
  let z = 10;
  let z = 10 + y;
</pre>

<h3>The += Operator</h3>
<p>This is an addition assignment operator that adds a value to a variable. For example:</p>
<pre>
  let a = 10; a += 5;
  let text = "Hi"; text += " there";
</pre>

<h3>The -= Operator</h3>
<p>This is a subtraction assignment operator that subtracts a value from a variable. For example:</p>
<pre>
  let m = 20;
  m -= 5;
</pre>

[...]

